      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 is a definitive example of front-midship engineering, preserved in a state that mirrors its factory delivery. Under the hood, the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine operates with surgical precision, maintaining optimal compression and seamless transition between the primary and secondary turbines. The chassis features a perfect 50:50 weight distribution, complemented by an untouched four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential that ensures neutral handling and maximum traction. The five-speed manual gearbox offers tight, mechanical engagement, while the vacuum system\u2014the heart of the FD's complex boost control\u2014is in flawless condition. This is a collector-grade vehicle for the purist who demands uncompromised analog performance and mechanical integrity.",
